source.excerpts.0.value: The latter were substantial and influential burghers , merchants and lawyers mostly , from the chief towns .Utrecht Gelderland , and Overyssel , as well as the Dutch 9 THE LIFEGUARDSMAN 144 violet perfume ; put on my amber velvet dress , a lace collar , my large gold bracelets : now I am She entered the drawing - room , where Captain Semeyns awaited her .I thank you , sir , most cordially for coming so politely at my Asking him to sit , she took her own place on the sofa .
source.excerpts.1.value: Haven ' t I and Barend been at your house every day for weeks past ? — then oughtn ' t you to come to ours ? And then , by our dinner - time he will have got your money for you , and will let you have So it was arranged between the two good women .Accordingly on Thursday morning , in the kitchen of Juff ' rouw Nagtegaal , who did all her household industry as well as all her marketing unassisted , there was such a fury of hot culinary processes , roasting , boiling , frying , and frizzling , with such clatter of dishes and pots , and a compound of savoury odours , that Barend could neither mind his books in the parlour nor his business in the shop .He went out to make a round of visits to his patients , instructing his shopman , Harmen , to go at noon to the Stadhuis , with the papers entrusted to him by Juffer Semeyns , and to bring the money and whatever else should be delivered delivered to her order at the Army Pay Office .
source.excerpts.2.value: found these lying behind the sofa .To whom did they belong ? and who was your visitor ? Was it that Alfred , or that Edwin ? You had their names on your lips last night , when you came in , reeking of brandy and tobacco .You had been roving about London , supping and drinking with them ! I was not asleep ; I heard all you said .
source.excerpts.3.value: Going to fetch it , she found in it a piece of money that she had not expected .Coming back to Brechtjen , with a smile of affectionate approval , she laid her hand upon the girl ' s fair head , kissed her fondly , and said to her — Now I know why there is such a smell of candleburning candleburning in our bedroom when I come upstairs at night , hours later than you do ! And now , dear child , I know why these cheeks of yours are so pale ! I do not wish you to work so hard ; but you are my own brave child ! No , mother , it is you who are answered Brechtjen , turning her face away , for her eyes were full of tears .Gertrude pressed her daughter ' s hand .

source.excerpts.4.value: She had a narrow escape of being knocked down by a clumsy porter with a cask of sugar on his back .They stood before a portable booth , on the little high shelf or stage of which they saw the figure of the Amsterdam Punch , namely , Jan Klaas , murderously beating , not his wife , but a dandy Frenchman , a laced , silken , scented courtier .Brechtjen observed stately carriages , with guards , at the door of the Stadhuis or Town Hall .
source.excerpts.5.value: Taking off her mantle , hat , and black silk mask , she threw them on the floor ; then her rich new dress of blue velvet and white satin ; and put her gold ornaments and jewelled ivory fan upon the table .There was a smell of tobacco - smoke from the clothes , and of brandy from her breath .She had been in the company of men who smoked and drank ; her own face was flushed , probably by strong liquor , as well as painted ; she yawned and hiccuped , and her tongue began to tell the evening ' s tale .
source.excerpts.6.value: Nelly heard her growth and her figure commended , after a careful survey .She was more intent on admiring the silken folds of her Aunt ' s dress , and revelling in the perfume of her scented kid gloves , and of her cambric handkerchief trimmed with lace .Aunt ! how much longer must I stay here ? If I belong to you , then my father and mother were not common people .
